Former Prime Minister and ODM leader Raila Odinga was granted a perfect Mashujaa day present after he was appointed an African Union High Representative for Infrastructure Development in Africa. In a statement dispatched from Addis Ababa, AU Chairman Moussa Faki Mahamat  said Odinga’s appointment is part of the African Union’s drive to expedite the integration of the continent through infrastructure in order to promote economic growth and sustainable development. President Uhuru Kenyatta congratulated Odinga on his new appointment terming it a great honour for Kenya.  